WEBVTT

00:02.383 --> 00:04.255
Dre: The word "nepotism"
 is defined as...

00:09.390 --> 00:12.513
The term originated
when Catholic popes and bishops

00:12.513 --> 00:13.974
used to give their nephews

00:13.974 --> 00:15.976
important positions
 in the church.

00:15.976 --> 00:18.689
Get it --
 "nephew", "nepotism"?

00:18.689 --> 00:19.770
[ Ding! ]

00:19.770 --> 00:21.021
Nepotism is what

00:21.021 --> 00:22.943
this country was built on --

00:22.943 --> 00:26.447
in politics,
 sports, entertainment,

00:26.447 --> 00:29.029
and even the manufacturing
 of affordable duck calls.

00:29.029 --> 00:30.071
[ Duck quacks ]

00:30.071 --> 00:31.532
But if you're not lucky enough

00:31.532 --> 00:32.783
to be hooked up like that,

00:32.783 --> 00:35.035
you have to do it
 all on your own,

00:35.035 --> 00:36.457
which can be tough.

00:37.658 --> 00:39.660
So I learned to work
 twice as hard

00:39.660 --> 00:41.462
to get what some
 of those nepotized people

00:41.462 --> 00:42.833
had given to them.

00:42.833 --> 00:47.668
And eventually,
 the hard work I did paid off.

00:47.668 --> 00:50.171
So I appreciate
 everything I got

00:50.171 --> 00:52.803
because I know I earned it.

00:52.803 --> 00:57.268
It built my character,
 and I want that for my kids,

00:57.268 --> 01:00.601
which is why they won't be
 using my connections

01:00.601 --> 01:02.443
to get any shortcuts in life.

01:02.443 --> 01:04.185
Oh! Dre, thank God
you're here.
 Mm-hmm?

01:04.185 --> 01:05.856
If Zoey is ever gonna
get into college,

01:05.856 --> 01:07.858
she is gonna need you
to use your connections

01:07.858 --> 01:09.530
to hook her up
with an internship.

01:09.530 --> 01:10.991
What?

01:16.036 --> 01:18.409
Zoey waited too long
to find a college internship,

01:18.409 --> 01:20.621
and the only way she's gonna
get one is if you help her.

01:20.621 --> 01:21.752
What?

01:21.752 --> 01:23.124
Well, why didn't she ask me
for my help?

01:23.124 --> 01:24.965
[ Camera shutter clicks ]
 I was gonna text you about it.

01:24.965 --> 01:26.467
I just got caught up
with something.

01:26.467 --> 01:27.668
Uh, Dad, uh...can you help me

01:27.668 --> 01:29.170
with that thing
Mom's talking about?

01:29.170 --> 01:30.381
Look at her, Bow.
 Mm-hmm.

01:30.381 --> 01:32.343
She expects everything
to be handed to her

01:32.343 --> 01:33.714
on a silver platter.

01:33.714 --> 01:34.845
But if she
wants something,

01:34.845 --> 01:36.977
she's gonna have
to go after it on her own.

01:36.977 --> 01:38.309
Just like
I did, Dad.

01:38.309 --> 01:41.312
I wanted a job,
so I went and got one.

01:41.312 --> 01:41.982
Nice!

01:41.982 --> 01:42.853
You're now looking at

01:42.853 --> 01:44.605
the newest team member

01:44.605 --> 01:46.147
of Pizza Possum.
 Huh.

01:46.147 --> 01:47.778
The premier
kids' arcade,

01:47.778 --> 01:50.110
playland,
and possum-themed eatery.

01:50.110 --> 01:51.732
Junior, what does this
have to do

01:51.732 --> 01:53.494
with what we're
talking about, hmm?

01:53.494 --> 01:56.997
Uh, everything?
I segued into it.

01:56.997 --> 01:59.620
I even used some
of the same words you use.

01:59.620 --> 02:01.412
Don't pay him
any attention.

02:01.412 --> 02:03.003
That is wonderful
that you got a job.

02:03.003 --> 02:04.375
I'm proud.
 Thanks, Mom.

02:04.375 --> 02:06.747
Hey, Zoey, I can
pull some strings

02:06.747 --> 02:09.460
and get you an internship
down at The Possum.

02:09.460 --> 02:13.174
[ Scoffs ] I would not
even want to own that place.

02:13.174 --> 02:16.517
See? No work ethic.
Complete bum.

02:16.517 --> 02:18.349
Well, Dre, she needs
something that looks good

02:18.349 --> 02:20.431
on her college application,
and quick.

02:20.431 --> 02:23.023
Uh, I feel like we got off
of my thing too fast.

02:23.023 --> 02:24.395
Okay, Junior,
enough, all right?

02:24.395 --> 02:26.357
We get it. You have a job
that nobody wants.

02:26.357 --> 02:28.359
Hey, look here.
You're a big shot.

02:28.359 --> 02:30.361
Why can't you get her
an internship at the hospital?

02:30.361 --> 02:32.112
You don't think
I tried?

02:32.112 --> 02:35.536
Yeah, if you could just give her
something really small,

02:35.536 --> 02:36.657
I'd really appreciate it.

02:36.657 --> 02:37.908
I'm sorry.
Who are you?

02:37.908 --> 02:39.660
R--
Uh, Rainbow Johnson.

02:39.660 --> 02:43.083
We've done like
300 surgeries together?

02:43.083 --> 02:44.495
I saved
your mother's life!

02:44.495 --> 02:46.957
Hmm. Seems like
I'd remember that.

02:48.419 --> 02:50.251
Dre, you have
so many connections.

02:50.251 --> 02:51.882
Why won't you use them
to help her?

02:51.882 --> 02:54.295
Because they are
  my connections.

02:54.295 --> 02:56.927
I had to hustle hard
to get my hookups.

02:56.927 --> 02:59.300
All for Dad, none for you.

02:59.300 --> 03:00.971
Got it? Good.

03:00.971 --> 03:03.224
Let's roll.

03:03.224 --> 03:05.226
You don't even like
red Gatorade.

03:05.226 --> 03:06.567
I don't need to like it.

03:06.567 --> 03:09.770
I got hooked up
because I am a trendsetter,

03:09.770 --> 03:11.572
a taste maker...

03:11.572 --> 03:12.693
and a hustler.

03:12.693 --> 03:15.446
Dre, you got hooked up

03:15.446 --> 03:18.489
because you got rear-ended
by a manager from BevMo.

03:18.489 --> 03:21.582
All I'm saying is that
if Zoey wants an internship,

03:21.582 --> 03:24.625
she's gonna have to put
in the work and get it herself.

03:24.625 --> 03:26.247
Let her get her own Gatorade
like I got mine.

03:26.247 --> 03:28.289
[ Scoffs ]

03:28.289 --> 03:29.540
Mm.

03:29.540 --> 03:31.171
Ugh!

03:31.171 --> 03:33.213
Should have
taken the money.

03:33.213 --> 03:35.135
They offered you money?!

03:35.135 --> 03:37.638
Diane: You've been
at Pizza Possum for two days.

03:37.638 --> 03:39.550
Why haven't you hooked us up
with prize tickets?

03:39.550 --> 03:41.011
We have 20.

03:41.011 --> 03:42.803
We're gonna need
about 500,000 more

03:42.803 --> 03:44.345
if we want
to get a lava lamp.

03:44.345 --> 03:46.517
Diane: I want something
sophisticated,

03:46.517 --> 03:49.149
like a hamburger phone
or brass knuckles.

03:49.149 --> 03:51.732
I can't be giving out favors
willy-nilly.

03:51.732 --> 03:53.734
I'm a valued employee.

03:53.734 --> 03:56.617
They don't just give this
 to anybody with a vest.

03:56.617 --> 03:59.660
Here, this opens all the
token machines and arcade games.

03:59.660 --> 04:01.822
I'll guard it
with my life, sir.

04:01.822 --> 04:03.073
Whatever.

04:03.073 --> 04:04.665
If you lose it,
use your fingernail.

04:04.665 --> 04:06.827
Give me the key!
I want the power.

04:06.827 --> 04:09.169
Sorry, guys,
but I can't help you.

04:09.169 --> 04:11.462
He's right.
He can't help you.

04:11.462 --> 04:14.505
He's got a new family now --
Corporate America.

04:14.505 --> 04:17.838
His mother is capitalism.
His father is greed.

04:17.838 --> 04:19.550
His sister
is the bott--
 Okay, stop!

04:19.550 --> 04:21.552
Just stop. We get it.

04:21.552 --> 04:24.805
Do not listen to him.
I am very proud of you, okay?

04:24.805 --> 04:28.228
Remember, Junior, you are more
than just an ill-fitting vest.

04:28.228 --> 04:29.350
Ill-fitting?

04:29.350 --> 04:30.851
You cannot possibly think
this looks good.

04:30.851 --> 04:32.152
What is that, burlap?

04:32.152 --> 04:34.445
It looks great.
You're great.

04:34.445 --> 04:36.987
So don't listen to anything
people are gonna say about you.

04:36.987 --> 04:38.319
Just ignore
everybody out there

04:38.319 --> 04:40.030
who's gonna call you
"Pizza Nerd,"

04:40.030 --> 04:42.613
"Name-Tag Boy," "Dummy."

04:42.613 --> 04:43.824
Who's calling me that?

04:43.824 --> 04:45.956
And people might be cruel
about the way

04:45.956 --> 04:48.078
your mouth hangs open
when you're listening.

04:48.078 --> 04:50.911
Ignore those people.

04:50.911 --> 04:52.623
Hold on.
Who is saying this stuff?

04:52.623 --> 04:54.214
People.

04:54.214 --> 04:56.256
Thanks, but I think
I'll be fine.

04:56.256 --> 04:57.418
Okay.

04:57.418 --> 04:58.839
I've got a job to do.

04:58.839 --> 04:59.920
Oh, boy.

05:03.263 --> 05:05.426
You're "people,"
aren't you?

05:05.426 --> 05:07.848
It's Mommy's job
to be "people."

05:07.848 --> 05:09.480
Dre: To be honest,
I was annoyed

05:09.480 --> 05:11.562
that Bow would even ask me
to help Zoey.

05:11.562 --> 05:13.774
I didn't use nepotism
to get to where I am.

05:13.774 --> 05:14.775
Why should my kids?

05:14.775 --> 05:16.026
You're right, Dre.

05:16.026 --> 05:17.988
Nepotism is disgusting.

05:17.988 --> 05:20.491
I mean, whatever happened
to good, old-fashioned

05:20.491 --> 05:21.862
strong work ethic.

05:21.862 --> 05:23.073
-Exactly.
-Mm-hmm.

05:23.073 --> 05:24.945
Take my little Connie --

05:24.945 --> 05:27.287
Now, he's not just gonna have
the CEO position handed to him.

05:27.287 --> 05:28.449
Damn straight.

05:28.449 --> 05:31.211
But...I am definitely gonna be
CEO.

05:31.211 --> 05:32.503
Of course.
You're my son.

05:32.503 --> 05:34.084
But you are gonna
have to work your way up

05:34.084 --> 05:35.626
from Senior Vice President.

05:35.626 --> 05:38.669
Hold up. I worked here 10 years
before I became SVP.

05:38.669 --> 05:39.840
He's SVP?

05:39.840 --> 05:41.552
Just of the urban stuff,
sweetheart.

05:41.552 --> 05:42.723
I want that, too.

05:42.723 --> 05:44.465
Mm...no, you don't.

05:44.465 --> 05:46.056
Josh: I only used
nepotism once --

05:46.056 --> 05:47.388
to make out
with my cousin.

05:47.388 --> 05:49.600
No, Josh,
that's incest.

05:49.600 --> 05:51.061
No, it's not.

05:51.061 --> 05:52.182
We were
on Martha's Vineyard,

05:52.182 --> 05:53.524
and she was getting
divorced.

05:53.524 --> 05:54.645
Disgusting.

05:54.645 --> 05:55.646
Charlie: I feel ya, Dre.

05:55.646 --> 05:57.357
I went from working
at Pan Am

05:57.357 --> 05:59.400
to slinging burgers
at a drive-in.

05:59.400 --> 06:01.281
Roller-skated
up to Janis Joplin.

06:01.281 --> 06:03.404
She asked me
to hold the onions.

06:03.404 --> 06:05.786
Man, I put a gang
of onions on there.

06:05.786 --> 06:08.539
[ Chuckling ] Trying to tell me
what to do.

06:08.539 --> 06:11.872
Pan Am and Janis Joplin --
Charlie, how old are you?

06:11.872 --> 06:13.454
Between 39 and 72.

06:13.454 --> 06:15.045
What?
 I wasn't allowed

06:15.045 --> 06:16.957
to see
my birth certificate --

06:16.957 --> 06:19.259
something about my father not
wanting me to know who he was.

06:19.259 --> 06:20.841
But the most important thing
is

06:20.841 --> 06:24.555
I became something --
Junior Account Manager.

06:24.555 --> 06:26.637
I work hard for everything
that I got --

06:26.637 --> 06:30.010
My Buick LeSabre,
my book of CDs, my TV.

06:30.010 --> 06:32.272
Well, almost my TV --

06:32.272 --> 06:34.314
Only 30 more payments
to the rental place.

06:34.314 --> 06:36.517
[ Ding! ]

06:36.517 --> 06:38.188
[ Ding! ]

06:38.188 --> 06:41.652
But at least I can say
I don't owe anyone anything.

06:41.652 --> 06:42.653
Except your ex-wife.

06:42.653 --> 06:43.614
And the government.

06:43.614 --> 06:44.485
And that rental place.

06:44.485 --> 06:46.076
And me
for lunch yesterday.

06:46.076 --> 06:47.788
Damn.

06:47.788 --> 06:49.409
I owe a lot of people.

06:49.409 --> 06:51.662
Dre, when I die,
buy me a headstone, all right?

06:51.662 --> 06:54.164
Don't -- Don't let them
bury me in the field.

06:54.164 --> 06:56.797
Field funerals aren't fun --
too many flies.

06:56.797 --> 06:58.499
And then it hit me --

06:58.499 --> 07:01.542
All the white guys at work had
 gotten ahead using nepotism,

07:01.542 --> 07:05.215
while Charlie is still paying
 off a $17,000 television.

07:05.215 --> 07:08.719
I couldn't let
 that happen to Zoey.

07:08.719 --> 07:10.601
Before you ask, yes,

07:10.601 --> 07:12.352
my knitting club
is making little bags

07:12.352 --> 07:13.554
to cover
broken parking meters,

07:13.554 --> 07:15.145
and, yes,
it was my idea.

07:15.145 --> 07:16.316
[ Sighs ]
 What's wrong with you?

07:16.316 --> 07:17.688
I went to work,

07:17.688 --> 07:19.860
brought love
and light to kids,

07:19.860 --> 07:22.442
then
I saw some things --

07:22.442 --> 07:24.905
things
I can never unsee.

07:26.276 --> 07:28.739
Hey, hey!
You don't dump old fries.

07:28.739 --> 07:30.330
You marry them.

07:30.330 --> 07:31.992
But the customer
licked the salt off

07:31.992 --> 07:33.453
and put them
back on their plate.

07:33.453 --> 07:34.915
Then they're low
in sodium.

07:34.915 --> 07:36.376
We're doing God's work.

07:36.376 --> 07:38.038
Junior: And that's not even
the worst of it.

07:38.038 --> 07:40.420
You know Pizza Possum's
best-selling food item,

07:40.420 --> 07:41.882
the Possum Blossom?

07:41.882 --> 07:44.424
You assume it's just
a whimsical name.

07:44.424 --> 07:46.386
It is not.

07:46.386 --> 07:49.089
Corporate America --
Anything to cut a corner.

07:49.089 --> 07:51.221
I'm going to shower.
I feel dirty.

07:51.221 --> 07:53.183
Ain't a loofah big enough
to wash your conscience.

07:53.183 --> 07:55.395
Oh, hey, Junior.

07:55.395 --> 07:56.937
How's it going
down at the P.P.?

07:56.937 --> 07:58.358
Did you have to use
that fancy key?

07:58.358 --> 07:59.560
Did you play
in the ball pit?

08:02.022 --> 08:04.064
Yep! All of that!

08:04.064 --> 08:05.986
Best job ever!

08:05.986 --> 08:07.157
[ Chuckles ]
 Awesome!

08:07.157 --> 08:09.409
Now go do your homework,
and whatever you do,

08:09.409 --> 08:12.112
don't look up
their Yelp reviews.

08:12.112 --> 08:13.203
Yay!

08:15.325 --> 08:17.037
Junior:
They're so innocent.

08:17.037 --> 08:18.749
They'd never
understand the truth.

08:18.749 --> 08:20.751
But you do.

08:20.751 --> 08:21.792
[ Whispers ] You do.

08:24.124 --> 08:27.427
Zoey, I have
the greatest news.

08:27.427 --> 08:29.630
Is it that you didn't
go out in that romper?

08:29.630 --> 08:32.683
That's definitely not it.
Ask anyone at my school.

08:32.683 --> 08:35.846
Okay, what I was
saying is that...
 Mm-hmm.

08:35.846 --> 08:38.808
...I got you an internship
at the hospital!

08:38.808 --> 08:40.480
Oh!
 I mean, I had to give up
my parking space,

08:40.480 --> 08:41.562
but I was, like,
one patient death away

08:41.562 --> 08:42.943
from losing it anyway,
so...
 [ Door opens ]

08:42.943 --> 08:43.984
You're amazing!
 Ahh!

08:43.984 --> 08:45.195
Thanks, Mom!
 Yay!

08:45.195 --> 08:46.817
[ Door closes ]
 Hey, everybody.

08:46.817 --> 08:48.609
I have some great news.

08:48.609 --> 08:50.741
What, that you didn't wear
those shoes all day long?

08:50.741 --> 08:52.452
[ Laughs ]

08:52.452 --> 08:54.655
Mom, that's mean.

08:54.655 --> 08:56.366
No, I --
 That's a shame.

08:56.366 --> 08:58.829
I pulled some strings
with a client,

08:58.829 --> 09:01.251
and I got Zoey
a fellowship

09:01.251 --> 09:03.253
at Teen Vogue.
 Oh.

09:03.253 --> 09:05.716
Oh, my God!
 Wh-- Hey!

09:05.716 --> 09:07.928
S-Sorry, Mom.
It's Teen Vogue.

09:07.928 --> 09:10.761
I was gonna find a way out of
your gross internship anyway.

09:10.761 --> 09:12.222
Hey, mine's gross, too,
all right?

09:12.222 --> 09:13.473
You're starting
in the mailroom --

09:13.473 --> 09:14.805
rock bottom.

09:14.805 --> 09:16.977
Still better than the top
of the hospital.

09:16.977 --> 09:19.139
Ahh!
Mm, there you go!

09:19.139 --> 09:21.141
Bye.

09:21.141 --> 09:22.773
Oh.

09:22.773 --> 09:24.815
Did, um...
Did you go out in that?

09:24.815 --> 09:27.277
Yes, I did.
 Hmm.

09:27.277 --> 09:29.069
Wha--
 Okay.

09:32.993 --> 09:33.864
Dre: I thought about it,

09:33.864 --> 09:34.955
and everyone else
has been using nepotism,

09:34.955 --> 09:37.077
and this is our first time that
we're in a position to use it.

09:37.077 --> 09:38.999
So you should be happy,

09:38.999 --> 09:42.082
because, thanks to me,
Zoey will never be

09:42.082 --> 09:45.375
a 72-year-old
Junior Account Manager

09:45.375 --> 09:48.048
who will be buried
in a field like Charlie.

09:48.048 --> 09:50.711
Wait, Dre. 72?

09:50.711 --> 09:54.054
[ "Quantum Leap" theme song ]

10:00.891 --> 10:02.222
Wow.

10:02.222 --> 10:04.104
Yeah, he'll still
never live long enough

10:04.104 --> 10:05.986
to pay for that TV.
-Hmm.

10:05.986 --> 10:08.568
I couldn't wait to bring Zoey
 over to Teen Vogue.

10:08.568 --> 10:10.570
They love me there because
 of all the great work

10:10.570 --> 10:11.692
I've done for them.

10:11.692 --> 10:13.233
-Dre!
-Oh!

10:13.233 --> 10:14.735
There he is --

10:14.735 --> 10:17.197
The man who talked us out
of our Paul Giamatti cover.

10:17.197 --> 10:19.539
Ugh! I don't know how
that got so much traction.

10:19.539 --> 10:21.331
Ooh, what
were you thinking?

10:21.331 --> 10:24.454
But, Neil,
this is my princess Zoey.
 Aww!

10:24.454 --> 10:26.376
I want you to treat her
like garbage, okay?

10:26.376 --> 10:28.628
Throw stuff on her --
clothes, hot coffee.

10:28.628 --> 10:30.510
[ Gasps ] Have her
make the hot coffee

10:30.510 --> 10:32.052
and throw it on her --
No, no. No, no, no.

10:32.052 --> 10:33.383
Have her throw it
on herself,

10:33.383 --> 10:35.055
because I know
you are a busy man.

10:35.055 --> 10:36.717
[ Whispers ]
And she's garbage.

10:36.717 --> 10:38.598
Nice to meet you.

10:38.598 --> 10:40.721
And, Neil,
  please do not let

10:40.721 --> 10:43.934
your love and adoration for me
spill over onto her.

10:43.934 --> 10:44.975
Put her
in the mailroom.

10:44.975 --> 10:46.356
We don't have a mailroom.

10:46.356 --> 10:47.938
Whatever.
Put her in the basement.

10:47.938 --> 10:50.190
Um, this isn't where
we make the clothes,

10:50.190 --> 10:51.772
but I hear ya.
 Mm!

10:51.772 --> 10:53.033
Come on, Zoey.

10:53.033 --> 10:54.534
Let me show you your pen.

10:54.534 --> 10:56.486
-Okay.
-Mm.

10:56.486 --> 10:58.038
It's really a cute desk
in the corner.

10:58.038 --> 10:59.700
Okay.
Is that vintage Givenchy?

10:59.700 --> 11:00.701
Good eye.

11:00.701 --> 11:02.913
-Thanks, I --
-Hey, peon! Quiet!

11:02.913 --> 11:04.955
Zip it! Neil, thank you.

11:06.246 --> 11:07.587
I'm sorry about him.

11:07.587 --> 11:09.169
Dr. Rambo.

11:09.169 --> 11:10.550
Rainbow.

11:10.550 --> 11:11.591
I'd go with "Rambo."

11:11.591 --> 11:13.553
Yeah, people
remember Rambo -- hero.

11:13.553 --> 11:15.385
[ Sighs ]
 Anyhow, we got a ton
of work to do.

11:15.385 --> 11:16.757
Where's that intern
you begged me to hire?

11:16.757 --> 11:18.929
I did beg,
and you did hire.

11:18.929 --> 11:20.600
[ Both chuckle ]

11:20.600 --> 11:23.143
S-- Uh, well, you just missed
her. She, uh -- Yeah.

11:23.143 --> 11:26.146
S-She's here,
just, you know...

11:26.146 --> 11:27.898
working hard.
 Oh, good.

11:27.898 --> 11:29.189
Well, if she's not,
it's on your head.

11:29.189 --> 11:30.400
I don't do favors lightly.

11:30.400 --> 11:34.614
And when I'm crossed,
I react with great vengeance.

11:34.614 --> 11:36.446
Ha!

11:36.446 --> 11:38.949
That is a fun thing
to learn about you.
 [ Chuckles ]

11:38.949 --> 11:40.160
Well, um, don't worry.

11:40.160 --> 11:43.123
I will oversee Zoey,
and it'll be like --

11:43.123 --> 11:45.375
like I'm doing
the job myself.

11:45.375 --> 11:47.087
All right, well,
just have her jiggle the legs

11:47.087 --> 11:48.538
of the big guy
at the end of the hall.

11:48.538 --> 11:50.791
Don't want
his bed sores to burst.
 Hmm.

11:50.791 --> 11:53.173
She will be
the person to do it.

11:56.336 --> 11:58.638
That arcade is awesome!

11:58.638 --> 12:01.391
And you know what makes it
even more awesome?

12:01.391 --> 12:04.264
Liberal amounts
of hand sanitizer!

12:04.264 --> 12:06.807
There we go.

12:06.807 --> 12:08.728
Wow, those are
a lot of tickets.

12:08.728 --> 12:11.731
Yeah, thanks for the tip
on Pound-A-Possum the other day.

12:11.731 --> 12:12.773
We had some good luck.

12:12.773 --> 12:14.274
Ow! Ow!

12:14.274 --> 12:16.116
This hurts so bad!

12:16.116 --> 12:17.527
How bad you want
that lava lamp, boy?

12:17.527 --> 12:18.568
I want it!

12:18.568 --> 12:21.031
Mm-hmm.
 Ow! Aah! Ow!

12:21.031 --> 12:22.662
Ooh, pizza!
 [ Gasps ]

12:22.662 --> 12:23.824
Don't eat that.

12:23.824 --> 12:26.666
But Pizza Possum pizza
is delicious.

12:26.666 --> 12:29.459
It's so spicy
and gamey.

12:29.459 --> 12:32.252
Yep, and it's pizza.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

12:32.252 --> 12:33.633
But you don't want
to fill up on that

12:33.633 --> 12:35.085
when there's
all those tickets to win.

12:35.085 --> 12:36.376
Yay!

12:36.376 --> 12:38.338
Sure.

12:38.338 --> 12:40.340
You saved your family
from Possum Pizza,

12:40.340 --> 12:42.012
but what about
these other kids?

12:44.014 --> 12:45.595
[ Whispers ]
For shame.

12:45.595 --> 12:47.517
You could really
clean this place up, man.

12:47.517 --> 12:49.729
Come on. Be a whistle-blower.
It's cool!

12:49.729 --> 12:51.231
[ Distorted ] Rachel Dolezal,

12:51.231 --> 12:54.694
the black president of
the Spokane branch of the NAACP,

12:54.694 --> 12:58.278
has been lying...
about her age.

12:58.278 --> 13:00.400
She was lying
about her race.

13:00.400 --> 13:02.492
The point is,
I was brave enough to stand up.

13:02.492 --> 13:04.494
You're right.

13:04.494 --> 13:07.707
I should be an upstander,
not a bystander.

13:09.249 --> 13:11.671
If I could get corporate
to clean up their act,

13:11.671 --> 13:13.914
this could be
the "Totally possum" place

13:13.914 --> 13:15.085
my hat says it is.

13:15.085 --> 13:17.217
[ Gasps ]
Don't eat that!

13:17.217 --> 13:18.378
What,
even the chopped salad?

13:18.378 --> 13:21.091
Especially
the chopped salad!

13:21.091 --> 13:24.094
There are no knives
in the kitchen.

13:24.094 --> 13:27.267
Everything is done
with hands and teeth.

13:27.267 --> 13:29.139
[ Gags ]

13:29.139 --> 13:31.601
Guess what happened to me
at Teen Vogue today.

13:31.601 --> 13:33.523
Hmm?
 I got promoted!

13:33.523 --> 13:35.105
Already?

13:35.105 --> 13:36.736
You've only been there a week.
-I know.

13:36.736 --> 13:39.529
They let me help pull looks
for an editorial shoot.

13:39.529 --> 13:41.151
That's amazing!

13:41.151 --> 13:43.443
But you're mailroom garbage!
Why isn't there coffee on you?

13:43.443 --> 13:44.865
Dre!

13:44.865 --> 13:46.867
T-They don't let garbage
pull looks!

13:46.867 --> 13:49.119
Well, they did today.

13:49.119 --> 13:51.041
I'm so proud of her!

13:51.041 --> 13:53.213
What--
 [ Sighs ]

13:53.213 --> 13:55.005
Aren't -- Aren't we
 proud of her?

13:55.005 --> 13:56.917
No.
You don't get it, do you?

13:56.917 --> 13:59.379
The only reason she got promoted
is because of me...
 Oh.

13:59.379 --> 14:01.171
...because I'm a superstar,
all right?

14:01.171 --> 14:02.883
A legend,
a wonderbread!

14:02.883 --> 14:05.675
[ Scoffs ] I think
you mean "a wunderkind."

14:05.675 --> 14:07.847
Obviously.
They're both great.
 Okay.

14:07.847 --> 14:10.020
All right, she does not
appreciate this.

14:10.020 --> 14:12.312
Now she's gonna think this is
how the real world works.

14:12.312 --> 14:14.024
Dre, just
give her this one.

14:15.275 --> 14:17.067
Of course
you don't get it.
 Oh, my God.

14:17.067 --> 14:19.739
You've never had to struggle
a day in your life.

14:19.739 --> 14:21.531
What?!

14:21.531 --> 14:24.864
Dre, I'm a black woman,
and I went to medical school,

14:24.864 --> 14:28.408
and I have four children
by a man-baby.

14:28.408 --> 14:30.790
So do not talk to me
about struggle, okay?

14:30.790 --> 14:32.122
You know what?

14:32.122 --> 14:33.833
You've been living it up here,
all right?
 I've b--

14:33.833 --> 14:36.666
Go to the refrigerator
and eat your fresh fruit.

14:36.666 --> 14:39.459
I was 22 years old
before I had fresh fruit.

14:39.459 --> 14:40.670
Okay.

14:40.670 --> 14:42.672
I'm "living it up."
Seriously?

14:42.672 --> 14:44.965
Every day is like
a nightmare with you.

14:44.965 --> 14:47.347
This is Andre Johnson Jr.

14:47.347 --> 14:50.640
I'm going to expose
Pizza Possum.

14:50.640 --> 14:51.891
Shouldn't have shown my face.

14:51.891 --> 14:53.273
I'll take that out.

14:53.273 --> 14:55.855
Remember to take that out!

14:55.855 --> 14:57.727
Okay, let's put these on.

15:01.821 --> 15:03.323
What are you doing?

15:03.323 --> 15:05.825
I...wear glasses now.
[ Chuckles ]

15:05.825 --> 15:07.367
They look like spy glasses.

15:07.367 --> 15:10.330
No, that's the style.
My sister works --

15:10.330 --> 15:11.791
Stop talking to me.

15:11.791 --> 15:13.793
Oof. Close call.

15:13.793 --> 15:15.665
Oh, and here we go.

15:15.665 --> 15:18.588
It's stakeout time,
and I'm in it for the long...

15:19.669 --> 15:22.882
Oh, my God!

15:22.882 --> 15:24.674
Happy birthday,
little Henry.

15:24.674 --> 15:27.347
I hope you wished
for herpes.

15:27.347 --> 15:29.849
So, maybe Bow was right,
 and I should just be happy

15:29.849 --> 15:31.721
that I'm able
 to help my daughter.

15:31.721 --> 15:33.643
Lots of people who start
 with a leg up

15:33.643 --> 15:35.265
are still good, hard workers.

15:35.265 --> 15:36.856
[ Snores ]

15:36.856 --> 15:38.648
Are you kidding me?!

15:38.648 --> 15:41.321
[ Whispers ] Shh! Do you know
how hard it is to get him down?!

15:41.321 --> 15:42.772
[ Grumbles ]

15:42.772 --> 15:45.065
Great, great.
Now you've woken him up.

15:45.065 --> 15:46.987
Mm. Am I CEO yet?

15:46.987 --> 15:48.828
Almost, sweetheart.

15:48.828 --> 15:51.701
Try to get a few more winks
before your lunch break.

15:51.701 --> 15:53.703
Here, have a sip-sip.

15:53.703 --> 15:56.126
Watching this fool take
 a mid-morning nap,

15:56.126 --> 15:58.878
I knew nepotism
 might get Zoey ahead,

15:58.878 --> 16:01.581
but it also puts her in danger
 of being useless.

16:01.581 --> 16:03.923
I couldn't let this happen
 to my daughter.

16:03.923 --> 16:07.047
♪♪

16:09.759 --> 16:11.591
I shouldn't have
sent that video.

16:11.591 --> 16:14.224
They know!
They're watching me!

16:14.224 --> 16:16.186
[ Whistling ]

16:18.938 --> 16:20.100
[ Whistling stops ]

16:22.692 --> 16:24.104
If they're
willing to kill you,

16:24.104 --> 16:25.025
then that's
the price we'll pay.

16:25.025 --> 16:26.156
What?

16:26.156 --> 16:28.568
I'm 16!
I-I've barely lived!

16:28.568 --> 16:31.161
Mm, a life sacrificed for honor
is the only life to live.

16:33.113 --> 16:34.784
Okay.

16:34.784 --> 16:37.497
If they silence me,
will you tell my story?

16:37.497 --> 16:40.120
Since you won't be able
to hold me to it, yes.

16:40.120 --> 16:41.711
So, I went over to Teen Vogue

16:41.711 --> 16:44.214
to save Zoey from becoming
 a worthless loser.

16:44.214 --> 16:45.215
Hey.

16:45.215 --> 16:47.387
I demand that you demote
Zoey Johnson.

16:47.387 --> 16:48.428
Excuse me?

16:48.428 --> 16:49.429
You are the editor,
right?

16:49.429 --> 16:50.800
Well, that depends --

16:50.800 --> 16:51.971
How crazy are you?

16:51.971 --> 16:53.893
I will not let you turn
my little girl

16:53.893 --> 16:55.305
into a useless,
entitled brat

16:55.305 --> 16:57.057
who is sleeping her way
to the top,

16:57.057 --> 16:58.228
like Connie Stevens.

16:58.228 --> 16:59.769
Okay, you're
that kind of crazy.

16:59.769 --> 17:01.231
Right,
I must sound ridiculous.

17:01.231 --> 17:03.693
I-I meant "napping".
Napping her way to the top.

17:03.693 --> 17:06.356
B-But the point is,
Zoey is unqualified

17:06.356 --> 17:08.568
and does not deserve
that promotion.

17:08.568 --> 17:09.949
Zoey: Thanks, Dad.

17:11.451 --> 17:14.414
That voice I heard belonged
to my daughter, didn't it?

17:14.414 --> 17:16.156
I believe that's why
she called you "Dad."

17:21.501 --> 17:23.333
What is going on, and why are
you making my staff cry?

17:23.333 --> 17:24.834
Hey, look, I'm doing this
for her own good.

17:24.834 --> 17:26.925
I-I know you're only giving Zoey
the special treatment

17:26.925 --> 17:28.428
because of my star status,

17:28.428 --> 17:30.590
my unparalleled genius,
my wunderkind.

17:30.590 --> 17:32.382
You have no idea who I am,
do you?

17:32.382 --> 17:33.803
No, I don't.
 Hmm.

17:33.803 --> 17:36.516
But that young lady
that you just insulted --

17:36.516 --> 17:38.678
She is a star.

17:38.678 --> 17:41.141
And if there's anyone getting
a promotion at Teen Vogue,

17:41.141 --> 17:43.353
it's because
they deserve it...

17:43.353 --> 17:45.815
except my assistant
whose dad owns the company.

17:45.815 --> 17:47.237
Wait, wait, wait.

17:47.237 --> 17:49.239
Did you just say
my daughter's a star?

17:49.239 --> 17:50.400
I did.

17:50.400 --> 17:52.652
And now
I'm calling security.

17:53.863 --> 17:56.196
Boom! I did it!

17:56.196 --> 17:58.788
I got an e-mail
from Pizza Possum HQ.

17:58.788 --> 18:01.581
"Dear Andre Johnson Jr"...

18:01.581 --> 18:02.662
You gave them your name.

18:02.662 --> 18:04.083
Bold.

18:04.083 --> 18:06.756
Well, I forgot to cut it
out of my exposé video.

18:06.756 --> 18:09.008
But listen --

18:09.008 --> 18:10.710
"Thank you for bringing
to our attention

18:10.710 --> 18:13.973
the unacceptable practices
at Branch 641.

18:13.973 --> 18:16.426
Be assured we will take
immediate action

18:16.426 --> 18:18.428
to rectify this situation.

18:18.428 --> 18:21.641
We will not play possum
with these accusations."

18:21.641 --> 18:22.892
I did it!

18:22.892 --> 18:24.184
Whistle blown!

18:24.184 --> 18:25.485
Junior...
 Whew.

18:25.485 --> 18:27.777
...today you made
a lot of kids happy.

18:29.189 --> 18:31.531
I hate you.
 You ruined my life.

18:31.531 --> 18:34.364
I just wanted them
to clean it up...for you.

18:34.364 --> 18:36.736
Get off you high horse,
Long Head.

18:36.736 --> 18:39.239
Who thinks pizza places
are clean, huh?

18:39.239 --> 18:41.621
Now our tickets
are worthless.

18:41.621 --> 18:44.584
Hey, at the end of the day,
I did the right thing,

18:44.584 --> 18:46.206
and I've got my integrity.

18:47.167 --> 18:49.509
Rainbow:
Thanks a lot, Pizza Nerd!

18:49.509 --> 18:51.301
[ Engine revs, tires screech ]

18:51.301 --> 18:53.383
Was that Mom?

18:53.383 --> 18:56.886
[ Scoffs ]
No, that was just "people."

18:59.058 --> 19:00.310
I'll send it to you.

19:00.310 --> 19:01.681
All right, that's great.
Thanks.

19:01.681 --> 19:02.892
Okay.

19:02.892 --> 19:04.764
Hey.

19:04.764 --> 19:07.397
Are you here
to throw coffee on me?

19:07.397 --> 19:08.478
Okay, look, I don't have
that much time

19:08.478 --> 19:10.610
before security finds me again,
so let me get this out.

19:10.610 --> 19:12.362
Mm-hmm?

19:12.362 --> 19:14.113
Elaine tells me
that you're a star.

19:14.113 --> 19:15.154
Well, I am.

19:15.154 --> 19:16.616
I'm kind of killing it
around here,

19:16.616 --> 19:18.488
despite what you
obviously think.

19:18.488 --> 19:19.989
I'm sorry.

19:19.989 --> 19:23.783
But Elaine says
you have great ideas.

19:23.783 --> 19:26.286
Re-creating Anna Wintour's
first Vogue cover --

19:26.286 --> 19:27.287
That's dope.

19:27.287 --> 19:28.878
How did you
come up with that?

19:28.878 --> 19:30.710
It just came to me.

19:30.710 --> 19:33.293
All of this stuff
sort of comes easy to me,

19:33.293 --> 19:35.295
like you
with advertising.

19:35.295 --> 19:38.348
Hey, I killed myself to get
where I am in advertising.

19:38.348 --> 19:39.799
When I was coming up,

19:39.799 --> 19:43.062
I had to fight
for every opportunity I got.

19:43.062 --> 19:46.065
And it was that fight
that made me appreciate it more.

19:46.065 --> 19:48.768
I guess that's all
I ever wanted for you.

19:48.768 --> 19:51.361
You think I don't
appreciate this job

19:51.361 --> 19:53.773
just because
you gave it to me?

19:53.773 --> 19:56.276
Look, sure, I hooked you up,
but my star power,

19:56.276 --> 19:57.907
it will only
get you so far.

19:57.907 --> 19:59.619
Ooh, okay, Dad,

19:59.619 --> 20:02.372
I don't think you have
as much star power as you think.

20:02.372 --> 20:04.374
Exactly!

20:04.374 --> 20:08.127
What I mean is that I can
get your foot in the door,

20:08.127 --> 20:10.169
but you're gonna have to go
the distance on your own.

20:10.169 --> 20:11.631
That's fine.

20:11.631 --> 20:14.714
And I'll work just as hard
to get to where I want to be

20:14.714 --> 20:18.137
as you worked
to get to where you are.

20:18.137 --> 20:19.138
[ Chuckles ]

20:19.138 --> 20:20.890
You will, won't you?

20:20.890 --> 20:22.972
Yeah, so just let me
do my thing.

20:22.972 --> 20:24.804
I'll figure it out.

20:24.804 --> 20:27.016
I won't be there
to catch you if you fall.

20:27.016 --> 20:28.978
Don't expect you to.

20:31.981 --> 20:33.653
What are you working on?

20:33.653 --> 20:36.406
I found this app where I can
put together looks

20:36.406 --> 20:38.197
to style my own
editorial shoot.
 Mm-hmm?

20:38.197 --> 20:40.199
I'm just practicing.

20:40.199 --> 20:42.071
That's what
I'm talking about.

20:45.825 --> 20:46.916
Ah, papaya.

20:46.916 --> 20:48.538
Must be nice.

20:48.538 --> 20:50.290
Didn't have that
till I was 30.

20:50.290 --> 20:51.631
Never had mango.

20:51.631 --> 20:53.713
Not now, Dre.

20:53.713 --> 20:55.925
I earned this.

20:55.925 --> 20:58.678
This is the first fresh thing
that I've seen all day.

20:58.678 --> 20:59.549
♪♪

21:01.721 --> 21:03.343
Ugh.

21:04.974 --> 21:06.185
[ Gags ]

21:06.185 --> 21:08.478
Oh, God! Oh, God! Okay!

21:08.478 --> 21:09.889
Oh, my -- Oh.

21:09.889 --> 21:11.771
Oh, God. It's pee.

21:11.771 --> 21:13.773
Interns work very hard.
-Mm-hmm.

21:13.773 --> 21:15.315
So hard, in fact,

21:15.315 --> 21:17.857
that they get promotions
and more hours,

21:17.857 --> 21:19.278
and then they just
start thinking about

21:19.278 --> 21:22.322
the benefits of...
amphetamines.

21:22.322 --> 21:23.573
Okay.
